    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "#[export]\nHint Immediate isisomorphism_components_of : typeclass_instances.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n(** When one of the functors is the identity functor, we fail to match correctly, because [apply] is stupid.  So we do its work for it. *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "#[export]\nHint Extern 10 (@IsIsomorphism _ _ _ (@components_of ?C ?D ?F ?G ?T ?x))\n=> apply (fun H' => @isisomorphism_components_of _ C D F G T H' x)\n   : typeclass_instances.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition inverse\n           C D (F G : Functor C D) (T : NaturalTransformation F G)\n           `{forall x, IsIsomorphism (T x)}\n: NaturalTransformation G F.",
